# Spec 007 — National Coverage at Launch

Status: Draft
Owner: <you>
Related: 002-data-enrichment (data shape), 004-backend-hardening (geofence
derives from the region index), 006-deployment (data ships in the image)

## Overview

The app is architected as national region-on-demand but ships with only three
states (WA, OH, CA). For a public launch, a visitor from any state should
find their region in the picker. This spec builds and commits the full
50-states + DC dataset and verifies the app behaves at that scale.

## Requirements

- **R1 — Full dataset.** `scripts/build_data.py` is run for every state in
  `STATE_SLUGS` (50 states + DC); per-state `{ST}.geojson` + `{ST}.zhvi.json`
  and the merged `regions.json` are committed. Skipped states (no ZHVI rows
  or failed geometry download) are re-run until none remain, or explicitly
  documented.
- **R2 — Size bounds.** Total committed state data stays under ~120 MB; any
  single state's geojson over ~8 MB is rebuilt with a higher simplification
  tolerance. The Docker image still builds and deploys on Render.
- **R3 — Picker at scale.** The region picker renders all ~51 entries
  alphabetically and remains usable (native select scrolls fine; a type-ahead
  filter is added only if real use feels bad).
- **R4 — Ramps and geofence nationwide.** Per-region adaptive quantile ramps
  (already runtime-computed) produce sensible shading for cheap and expensive
  states alike; the spec-004 geofence accepts work locations in every loaded
  state — including AK and HI — because it derives from the region index.

## Non-functional / Constraints

- Source data terms unchanged (free/aggregate, attribution in README).
- `lru_cache(maxsize=8)` on state stores remains the memory bound; bump only
  if eviction thrash appears in production logs.
- Raw downloads (~1 GB) are never committed (`scripts/raw` ignored).

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] `/api/regions` returns ~51 entries; every entry loads a choropleth.
- [ ] Five dispersed states spot-checked live (incl. HI and AK): choropleth
      shades, popups populate, isochrone works at an in-state work location.
- [ ] Largest committed state geojson ≤ ~8 MB; total `data/states` ≤ ~120 MB.
- [ ] Backend tests pass against the full dataset (`pytest` uses fixtures,
      plus a manual `uvicorn` smoke against real data).
- [ ] The region picker lists states alphabetically and selection flies the
      map to the region.

## Out of Scope (explicit)

- Automated/monthly data refresh (manual re-run of the build script for now).
- Redfin $/sqft for all states (optional flag; can be added in a later run).
- Territories beyond DC (PR, GU, VI — no OpenDataDE geometries).

## Verification notes

R1 → build log + file listing; R2 → size report + Docker build; R3/R4 → live
spot-checks on the deployed URL. The human walks the criteria; the
implementing agent does not self-certify done.
